      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "I like to conditionalize it (in zsh) with <code>if &#47;usr&#47;libexec&#47;java_home &amp;&gt; &#47;dev&#47;null; then export JAVA_HOME=$(&#47;usr&#47;libexec&#47;java_home); fi</code>, so I can use the same .rc file on multiple machines whether they have the JDK installed or not. Unconditionalized; you&#39;ll get a warning on each shell startup."
