    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 15,
    "last_activity_date" : 1423773615,
    "creation_date" : 1423773615,
    "answer_id" : 28487345,
    "question_id" : 1348842,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I'm on Mac OS 10.6.8</p>\n\n<p>The easiest solution works for me is simply put in</p>\n\n<pre><code>$ export JAVA_HOME=$(/usr/libexec/java_home)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>To test whether it works, put in</p>\n\n<pre><code>$ echo $JAVA_HOME\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>it shows</p>\n\n<pre><code>/System/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/1.6.0.jdk/Contents/Home\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>you can also test </p>\n\n<pre><code>$ which java\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6289460,
      "reputation" : 111,
      "user_id" : 4887626,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0888c3af7d967de8c3f890d1bef07f10?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "P&#225;lossy L&#225;szl&#243;",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4887626/p%c3%a1lossy-l%c3%a1szl%c3%b3"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 8,
    "last_activity_date" : 1549466576,
    "last_edit_date" : 1549466576,
    "creation_date" : 1431352378,
    "answer_id" : 30169515,
    "question_id" : 1348842,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>That above works not any more in YOSEMITE for GRAPHICAL APPLICATIONS! Like eclipse, or anything started with Spotlight. (.bash_profile, launchd.conf works for terminal sessions only.) \nBefore starting eclipse, just open a terminal window, and give out the following command:</p>\n\n<pre><code>launchctl setenv JAVA_HOME /Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk1.7.0_45.jdk/Contents/Home\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>(With your installation path! Perhaps works with $(/usr/libexec/java_home) instead of the full path too.)</p>\n\n<p>View the whole excellent article about the permanent solution here:\n<a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/25385934/setting-environment-variables-via-launchd-conf-no-longer-works-in-os-x-yosemite\">Setting environment variables via launchd.conf no longer works in OS X Yosemite/El Capitan/macOS Sierra?</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1581969,
      "reputation" : 70,
      "user_id" : 1467169,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e7fef4e7ce320bb6ecccf48295335e3c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Shirow",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1467169/shirow"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1444765335,
    "last_edit_date" : 1495540049,
    "creation_date" : 1444765335,
    "answer_id" : 33111263,
    "question_id" : 1348842,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I've found this <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/19582689/1467169\">stack</a> to help, i was having the same issue and i could fix:</p>\n\n<p>My java path was here:</p>\n\n<p><code>/Library/Internet Plug-Ins/JavaAppletPlugin.plugin/Contents/Home</code></p>\n\n<p>and was needed to put into my <code>.bash_profile</code>:</p>\n\n<p><code>export JAVA_HOME=\\\"/Library/Internet Plug-Ins/JavaAppletPlugin.plugin/Contents/Home\\\"</code></p>\n\n<p>Hope help</p>\n"
  }, {
